76561198271741107,Recommended,245430,23174252,"Posted: 23 May, 2016",all,adam_renaldo,"I played the game years ago, but never completed it.  Bought it again so I could finally finish the game. A thoroughly enjoyable, but very difficult, crpg.  The amount of race/class combinations and abilities is astounding.  The puzzles are almost impossible to figure out without the hint book.  Luckily, you get the hint book for free in the program's file folder.  Expect to reload saves often.I imported a party from Wizardry 6.  One downside is that it took a very long time before I found weapons and armor better than what I had imported with my party from the previous game. So a lot of the early treasure seems a bit worthless.It takes a long time to finish this game.  Especially if you don't download one of the many save game file editors that are available. Expect to spend years trying to beat the game if you don't use the hint book. Some of the mazes are extremely complicated.You certainly get a sense of accomplishment when you finally do complete the game.Recommended if you like Dungeons and Dragons, but want a few more options when leveling your character.  If you liked ""Eye of the Beholder"" or Wizardry 6, you'll probably like this as well.  Just keep in mind that the puzzles and mazes are significantly more complicated than ""Eye of the Beholder.""   Certainly beatable with the use of the hint book."
